<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title> My HTML Notes </title>
  </head>
      
<body>
  <h1>My HTML Notes </h1>
  <p>All text must be letters, numbers, and symbols.</p>
  
<hr>

<p><strong> Mark up: </strong> Text that has a special meaning.
- must start and end with a tag. </p>
  
<p>Italics: '< em >' for <em>italics</em> '< /em >'</p>
  
<p>Bold: '< strong >' for <strong>bold</strong> '< /strong >'</p>
  
<p>Highlight: '< mark >' for  <mark>  hightlighting  </mark>  '< /mark >'</p>
  
<p>Subscript:
<br>
'< sub >' <sub> located on the bottom of the line </sub> '< /sub >'</p>
      
<p>Superscript:
<br>
'< sup >' <sup> located on the top of the line  </sup> '< /sup ></p>
  
<hr>

<p> <strong> Lists: </strong> Must have end tags, but the items in the list use: '< li >' and do not need end markings.
  <ul> 
    <li>Unordered Lists: '< ul >'
    <li> Ordered Lists: '< ol >'
  </ul>
</p>
      
<p>Must have end tags, but the items '< li >' do not need end markings.</p>

<hr>

<div>
<p>Break: '< br > doesn't need an end tag, but just creates a line break. 
<br><br> 
-- Use '< br >< br >' to create a space between 2 lines. </p>

<p>Paragraph: '< p >' needs the ened tag '< /p > to create an element.</p>

<p>Divide: '< div >' can create a an element with multiple nested paragraphs inside.</p>

<p>Headings: '< h # >' creates different size headins. Use numbers 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, or 6 <br>(1 - biggest, 6 - smallest).</p>
</div>
  
<hr>
  
<p><strong>How to add a link:</strong><br>
'< a href = "http(s)://website.com/" > Text for link < /a >'
<br>(example:<a href="http://www.gmail.com/">Gmail</a>)</p>
  
<p> <strong>How to add an image link:</strong><br>
'< img src="link" alt="Text name >
  <br><br>
Example: 
<br>
<img src="https://placebear.com/200/150" alt="Bear Photo">
<br><br>
Note: After ".com/" the numbers 200/150 or 800/600 indicate the size of the photo.</p>
  
</body>
</html>
